{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.32",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 32,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 32",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 32 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:1",
      "text": "So these three men ceased to answer Job, because he was righteous in his own eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:2",
      "text": "Then Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite, of the family of Ram, became angry. He was angry at Job because he justified himself rather than God;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:3",
      "text": "he was angry also at Job's three friends because they had found no answer, although they had declared Job to be in the wrong.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:4",
      "text": "Now Elihu had waited to speak to Job because they were older than he.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:5",
      "text": "And when Elihu saw that there was no answer in the mouth of these three men, he became angry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:6",
      "text": "And Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite answered: “I am young in years, and you are aged; therefore I was timid and afraid to declare my opinion to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:7",
      "text": "I said, ‘Let days speak, and many years teach wisdom.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:8",
      "text": "But it is the spirit in a man, the breath of the Almighty, that makes him understand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:9",
      "text": "It is not the old that are wise, nor the aged that understand what is right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:10",
      "text": "Therefore I say, ‘Listen to me; let me also declare my opinion.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:11",
      "text": "“Behold, I waited for your words, I listened for your wise sayings, while you searched out what to say.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:12",
      "text": "I gave you my attention, and, behold, there was none that confuted Job, or that answered his words, among you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:13",
      "text": "Beware lest you say, ‘We have found wisdom; God may vanquish him, not man.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:14",
      "text": "He has not directed his words against me, and I will not answer him with your speeches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:15",
      "text": "“They are discomfited, they answer no more; they have not a word to say.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:16",
      "text": "And shall I wait, because they do not speak, because they stand there, and answer no more?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:17",
      "text": "I also will give my answer; I also will declare my opinion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:18",
      "text": "For I am full of words, the spirit within me constrains me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:19",
      "text": "Behold, my heart is like wine that has no vent; like new wineskins, it is ready to burst.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:20",
      "text": "I must speak, that I may find relief; I must open my lips and answer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:21",
      "text": "I will not show partiality to any person or use flattery toward any man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.32.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:22",
      "text": "For I do not know how to flatter, else would my Maker soon put an end to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
